articles.description: Fourth-ranked Xavier will try to extend its winning streak to nine games and maintain its slim hold on first place in the Big East Conference on Wednesday night when the Musketeers welcome Seton Hall to the Cintas Center.
articles.headline: Xavier's 4 Musketeers seek ninth straight victory

articles.description: Daniel Gafford scored 19 points to lead four Arkansas players in double figures Tuesday night as the Razorbacks defeated Mississippi 75-64.
articles.headline: Gafford, Hall lead Arkansas past Ole Miss, 75-64

images.caption: Arkansas head coach Mike Anderson talks about what the bench was able to provide and how the Hogs got it done defensively against Ole Miss.
images.name: Anderson: 'Real proud with the effort of our guys'

articles.description: Antwon Lillard sank three free throws after he was fouled on a 3-point attempt in the final seconds and Bowling Green rallied to beat Western Michigan 83-81 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Lillard sinks late FTs, Bowling Green rallies for 83-81 win

articles.description: Freshman Ray Salnave scored a career-high 21 points with four assists, Louie Pillari came off the bench to score 17 and Monmouth breezed to a 73-57 victory over Saint Peter's on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Salnave, Pillari lead Monmouth past Saint Peter's 73-57

articles.description: Udoka Azubuike leads the No. 13 Jayhawks with 19 points to edge the Cyclones 83-77.
articles.headline: Kansas holds off Iowa State on the road

images.caption: Udoka Azubuike leads the No. 13 Jayhawks with 19 points to edge the Cyclones 83-77.
images.name: Kansas holds off Iowa State on the road

articles.description: Trae Young is ice-cold from field, shooting 4-of-16 and scoring 19 points, as the No. 7 Red Raiders defeat the No. 23 Sooners 88-78.
articles.headline: Oklahoma falls to Texas Tech, for fourth consecutive loss

videos.description: Aaron Epps gets the pass in the corner and fools his defender with the pump fake leading to a wide-open three in the corner.
videos.headline: Epps drills 3-pointer to extend Tigers' lead into half

videos.description: PJ Washington gets the feed down low and towers over the defender for the one-handed throw down.
videos.headline: Washington shakes the rim with one-handed jam

videos.description: PJ Washington swats away the Tigers' shot resulting in a turnover in favor of the Wildcats.
videos.headline: Washington is a new resident of block city

videos.description: Duop Reath hits the open three from the top of the arc to give the Tigers the advantage over Kentucky.
videos.headline: Reath three gives LSU the lead

videos.description: Duop Reath gets the feed underneath and jams it home to keep the Tigers right in it with No. 17 Kentucky.
videos.headline: Reath shakes the rim to tie game

videos.description: LSU looks to Brandon Sampson for the last shot, but his 3-point attempt hits the front of the rim and bounces out giving Kentucky the win.
videos.headline: Kentucky survives as LSU's final shot just misses

videos.description: No. 17 Kentucky uses strong performances from PJ Washington and Kevin Knox to pull out the close win against LSU.
videos.headline: Kentucky fights off LSU in a hard-fought victory

videos.description: Head coach John Calipari and freshman PJ Washington break down highlights from Kentucky's victory against the Tigers.
videos.headline: Calipari, Washington talk road win vs. LSU

videos.description: LSU's Brandon Sampson bricks a 3-pointer as time expires to finish Kentucky's 74-71 victory on the road.
videos.headline: Kentucky escapes against LSU
